Privacy Policy
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how your data is collected, used, and protected when you interact with our Discord bot. By using the bot, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described in this policy.

2. Data Collection
The bot collects minimal user data to provide functionality. Specifically, the bot may collect:

User ID: Used to track user-specific commands and handle cooldowns.
Message Content: The content of messages sent to the bot is processed to provide responses, such as retrieving guild information or handling commands.
Command Usage: Data on which commands you use (e.g., .merc, .benz) for cooldown purposes and logging.
3. Data Usage
The data collected is used solely for the purpose of:

Responding to commands and requests made by users.
Managing cooldowns and user interactions.
Providing personalized responses, such as guild information, based on the commands.
4. Data Storage
All collected data is stored temporarily in memory (such as for cooldowns or tracking message content) and is not retained for any longer than necessary for the operation of the bot.

5. Data Sharing
We do not share any collected data with third parties. The bot's operations and data are private to your interaction with it on Discord.

6. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the Internet is completely secure.

7. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Request the deletion of your data by stopping interactions with the bot.
Not provide personal data if you prefer not to engage with the bot.
8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When changes are made, the updated policy will be posted with the "last updated" date.
